inheritedMembers.summary: Gets a flag that indicates that the data row should only be run explicitly. If the value is null, then it inherits its explicitness from the value of .
Gets the reason for skipping this row of data; if null is returned, then the data row isn't skipped.
Gets the display name for the test (replacing the default behavior, which would be to use or , or falling back to the default test display name based on and in the configuration file).
A value greater than zero marks the test as having a timeout, and gets or sets the timeout (in milliseconds). A non-null value here overrides any inherited value from the or the .
Gets or sets the traits for the theory data row.
